==English==

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/pʌnt/}}
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ʌnt|-ʌnt]]

===Etymology 1===
From {{L.}} ''[[ponto]]'' ‘Gaulish flat-bottomed boat’.

====Noun====
{{en-noun}}
# {{nautical}}: A [[pontoon]]; a narrow shallow boat propelled by a pole.

===Etymology 2===
Probably a dialectal variant of [[bunt]].

====Verb====
{{en-verb}}
# (sport) To [[kick]] a ball dropped from the hands before it hits the ground.

====Noun====
{{en-noun}}
# (sport) A [[drop-kick]].

===Etymology 3===
From French ''[[ponte]]'' or Spanish ''[[ponto]]'' ‘point’.

====Noun====
{{en-noun}}

# A point in the game of [[faro]].
# A bet or wager.
# ''(metaphorical):'' A highly speculative investment or other commitment, a wild guess.

====See Also====
*[[punter]]

